## Modular Design Analysis (pre-implementation)

### Existing Views / ViewModels Found
- `LSCard` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSCard.swift`) — reusable container for `color.surface.card`, radius, elevation; should own card surface styling.
- `LSText` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSText.swift`) — tokenized typography/content-color rendering for title/subtitle/meta.
- `LSAvatar` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSAvatar.swift`) — leading avatar atom for list-row avatar variant.
- `LSIcon` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSIcon.swift`) — leading/trailing icon atom for list-row icon and chevron affordances.
- `LSDivider` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSDivider.swift`) — tokenized separator for grouped row/story compositions.
- `LSButton` + `LSButtonStyle` (`ios/LaneShadow/Views/Atoms/LSButton.swift`) — tokenized trailing button action in list-row variant.
- `LSTagPill` / `LSFilterChip` / `LSSuggestionChip` molecule patterns — current molecule composition style and source-inspection testing patterns to mirror.
- No `*ViewModel.swift` / `*Repository.swift` / `*Model.swift` patterns discovered for this molecule slice.

### Reuse Opportunities (Rule of 2 from `dry-methodology`)
- List-row leading slot pattern (icon or avatar) appears across row variants, so I’ll extract a single leading renderer in `LSListRow` instead of duplicate branches per story.
- List-row trailing slot pattern (chevron/toggle/button/icon/none) appears across row variants, so I’ll centralize trailing rendering logic in one enum switch.
- Content-card optional row stack (subtitle/meta/chips/actions) appears in multiple story variants; I’ll implement one slot-based API to avoid variant-specific duplicate views.

### Unmodular Code Flags
- No unmodular code flags in current in-scope files because `LSContentCard.swift` and `LSListRow.swift` do not exist yet.
- For this task scope, implementation will enforce: no literal colors, no literal typography, no deprecated `.foregroundColor`, no `Font.system` in the two molecule files.

### Implementation Plan
1. RED: Add `LSContentCardTests` and `LSListRowTests` that reference new molecule APIs, atom composition expectations, story registration expectations (10 total), tap-once behavior, and no-forbidden-API source checks; run tests to fail.
2. GREEN: Implement `LSContentCard` and `LSListRow` with atom-only composition and token-driven spacing/min-touch-target.
3. GREEN: Add `LSContentCardStory`, `LSListRowStory`, update `MoleculesStories` and `ios/project.yml` entries.
4. REFACTOR: tighten API naming/slot helpers without behavior changes.
5. Validate: `swiftformat --lint`, `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, forbidden-pattern grep, generate project if needed, visual verification screenshot, write `ai-specs/UC-MOL-01/ios-learnings.md`, then commit.
